Text: (Enter Willy Loman. He is past sixty years of age, dressed quietly...)
It's all right. I came back.
Why? What happened? Did something happen, Willy?
You didn't smash the car, did you?
I said nothing happened. Didn't you hear me?
I'm tired to the death. I couldn't make it. I just couldn't make it, Linda.
(The flute plays on. He hears it but is not aware of it.)
Psychometric_Note: The Incidental Music of the Past
